radiographic_examinations.findings: A 1.4 x 1.4 cm T2 hyperintense lesion in segment 5 consistent with a cyst or biliary hamartoma; mild hydronephrosis of the right kidney; a mildly dilated, straightened appendix measuring 7.7 mm; no periappendiceal fat stranding; mild wall thickening of the appendix; normal remaining small and large bowel; T2 hypointense area along the anterior uterus consistent with a uterine contraction; gravid uterus with intrauterine pregnancy in breech position; fundal placenta present; cervix within normal limits; no free fluid or lymphadenopathy.
